  "prompt": "If I consumed 1 pint of alcohol, for 5 days in a row, but stopped 4 to 5 days before an etg test will I pass?",
  "response": "While it's difficult to give a definitive answer, ethyl glucuronide (EtG) is a metabolite of alcohol that can be detected in urine tests. EtG can typically be detected for up to 48 hours after alcohol consumption, but in some cases, it can be found for longer, especially with heavy and chronic drinking. \n\nIn general, for someone consuming a significant amount of alcohol like 1 pint per day for consecutive days, it's possible that EtG could still be detectable in your system 4 to 5 days after stopping, especially if your body takes longer to metabolize alcohol due to various factors (like your metabolism, hydration level, overall health, etc.).\n\nIf you have concerns about passing an EtG test, it might be best to consult with a healthcare professional or a testing expert for personalized advice.",
